citeinfo.othercit: No major changes since previous version.

descript.abstract: The City Council Districts are the result of the recent redistricting process, which takes place every ten years to reflect population changes reported in the 2000 Census. These geographies were redrawn by the New York City Council Redistricting Commission.
descript.purpose: These districts were created by the Department of City Planning to aid city agencies in administering public services.

idinfo.accconst: The data is freely available to all New York City agencies and the public.
idinfo.useconst: While all possible measures have been taken to ensure the accuracy of this data, the NYC Department of City Planning and the City of New York assume no responsibility for the accuracy of this data. All users should independently verify the accuracy of the data for their purposes.
